# State Management

## Two-track Architecture

| Track | Tool | Use For |
|---|---|---|
| Global / persistent UI state | Redux Toolkit + redux-saga | Auth session, user profile |
| Server / async data | TanStack React Query | API calls, caching |

---

## Redux Feature Structure

Each feature lives in `src/features/<name>/` with these files:

```
features/auth/
├── auth.actions.ts     # createRequestActions triplets
├── auth.saga.ts        # watchers + workers
├── auth.slice.ts       # state shape + extraReducers
├── auth.selector.ts    # memoized selectors
├── auth.helpers.ts     # pure helper functions
└── index.ts            # barrel export
```

### Actions — use `createRequestActions`

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — generates request / success / failure actions automatically
export const signInActions = createRequestActions<SignInPayload, SignInResponse>(
  'auth/signIn',
);

// ❌ BAD — manually creating action creators
const signInRequest = createAction<SignInPayload>('auth/signInRequest');
```

### Saga — use `createRequestSaga`

```ts
const signInSaga = createRequestSaga(signInActions, authService.signIn);

export function* authSaga() {
  yield takeLatest(signInActions.request, signInSaga);
}
```

### Slice — use `buildRequest` helper

```ts
const authSlice = createSlice({
  name: 'auth',
  initialState,
  reducers: { logout: () => initialState },
  extraReducers: builder => {
    buildRequest(builder, signInActions, (state, action) => {
      state.token = action.payload.token;
    });
  },
});
```

### Selectors — always memoize with `createSelector`

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export const selectIsAuthenticated = createSelector(
  selectAuthToken,
  token => !!token,
);

// ❌ BAD — inline derivation without memoization
const isAuth = useAppSelector(state => !!state.auth.token);
```

